ts my walk with the practice of Cleansing. While it is practiced different today, isn\'t it time to update my brush? Meaning: Evolve. Learn. Try anew, and teach what was once known.\r\n','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(10119537,1409812964,3070,637534208,43,'Tears of a Lizard',0,41,11,-6240,-2571,'A lizardress made me cry; she saw a spiny, little lizard; whose skin was rather dry; she told me I was ugly; and it made me cry; the lizard ran away from me; because she made me cry; the rude basilisk just took off; without telling me \"goodbye\"','2016-10-03 02:03:22'),(1891829,1325926884,3070,1728053248,39,'Ashes to Ashes',0,47,14,-9802,2498,'My take on the figurine of a fallen dragon: This symbolizes the struggle between protecting what you\'ve raised, and what you\'ve lost. The one time high-flying, highly suspicious, but mighty dragon had been slain by his own Caretaker. What most find cryptic and destroyed, I find inspiring. While this dragon will never fly again, an honest understanding will be born from it\'s ashes.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(1891861,1325926884,3070,1728053248,39,'Family Ties',0,47,14,-9844,2536,'An evaluation of the \'Burning, Family Tree\' art piece: Popularity and lust do not always promise longevity, respect, and lasting bonds. My taste for the big life, the love and adoration of peers, and the acquisition of intermediate and personal titles proven not to stand the test of time. Relationships lost, souls shattered, and dreamers gone. Was it worth it? Maybe. But then again. . . . Obviously not. Nevermore to venture beyond the customs of decently honest bonds. Blow, the winds of change.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(1893735,66233,3254780671,0,0,'Vial of Dark Liquid',0,17,25,293,-12134,'A vial of an unknown oily dark substance.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(1907410,4629,13437953,0,0,'PoR Flag',0,23,4,195,-8619,'','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(1907408,4501,13437953,0,0,'KoES Flag',0,23,4,102,-8591,'','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(12719298,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,49,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:27'),(12719297,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,49,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:27'),(12719296,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,49,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:27'),(12719295,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,49,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:27'),(12719294,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,49,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:27'),(12719293,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,49,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:27'),(12719292,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,49,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:27'),(12719291,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,49,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:27'),(1907407,4181,13437953,0,0,'AoE Flag',0,23,4,365,-8232,'','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2673183,3876063716,3070,4160749568,39,'FS Art Details (1)',0,41,20,3771,1006,'\r\nOrbit 10: Loudmouth (1min + 1 per plateau)Cost: 10Lucidity\r\nOrbit 15: Extrasensory (m) (5min + 5 per plateau, On/Off Functionality) Cost: 5 Lucidity\r\nOrbit 20: Butterfingers (Evoke speed matching Push) Cost: 15 Lucidity\r\nOrbit 25: Scramble (Evoke speed significantly slower than push) Cost: 20 Lucidity\r\nOrbit 30: Silence (m) (1 min + 1 per plateau) Cost: 10 Lucidity\r\nOrbit 35: Ventriloquism (Invisible evoke, medium-long length) Cost: 10 Lucidity','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(1934666,5909,13437953,0,0,'Cracked Egg Piece',0,17,25,-610,-13034,'','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2087598,789055976,2818,2231369728,39,'Myrdian Sun (2)',0,41,6,-2605,-7413,'Novgorad, Ms Xtreme, Ravenlunatic, Ritterwulf, Plato, Macky, Magnet, Ashling, Thornack, CoRrUpTiOn, rayvenfire all in the same armor colors, (abyss Night), wiped the floor with the Darks.  It was that evening that my journy towards being a protector began.  Despite what some may think; as small as it was; PoR did not pursue me to join.  Instead they focused on teaching me of the dream. Helped me to learn all the major beliefs, the various bodies of the dream (wordsmiths, FrS council, elders etc). ','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(1934414,501,13437953,0,0,'Ancient Skull',0,17,25,137,-13015,'An aged skull attached to a few inches of the spinal cord.  ','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(12718189,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,22,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:00'),(1958727,117508153,50332257,0,0,'Pearl of Perception',0,22,22,-8916,-7727,'A small burning star of pure Insight. Within a glass containment orb is night colored, burning glass. Within the energy there seems to be a small orb of physical matter giving it shape, even though it seems there is more to it. The Talisman is completely cold to the touch but seems to change with your own thoughts. Your focus increases exponentially. The sound of your ears underwater seems forced upon you from time to time when it is touched.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(12718154,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,21,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:17:59'),(2929823,526820,3070,1107296256,39,'Changes - The City',0,41,19,-4309,-484,'As far as specific places in the dream. There are no longer focus-specific gens for 20s or 30s within the Rifts and the various 2nd sphere areas. Likewise, your personal vaults have been lost to you, as well as any contents within, significantly increasing the reliance on pack management, or house vaults. The ability to Planesmith has been lost or not rediscovered, believed to be because of the City\'s ancient nature and stability. It is commonly believed our City was younger, and thus more susceptible...','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(12718266,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,24,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:02'),(12718265,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,24,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:02'),(2200339,1711802852,3070,1627389952,41,'Who Am I ? ~ 4',0,41,6,-2514,-7844,'My longing for companionship and family must have simply over taken me..and to my delight, some 17 or 18 years ago, I joined you all in this city of dreams. Here, I found that companionship, family, a sense of belonging, have achieved wonderous things, surreal things, but have also suffered heart ache and loss...though I would not trade it for the world. This piece of me..I bequeath to you, so that you may know who I am...why I love, why I laugh, why I cry, and why I dream..... ~C','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2077751,84412900,3476478,3523215360,2578472,'Train50:Jerulan',0,41,23,-3831,1889,'Encouraging dreamers to improve their train is one of the reasons I am here. I would like to see what you feel is worthy of 50 plateaus. Sample task the GateKeepers in your house three arts to 50 each, and let me see what you come up with. And don\'t be boring.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2087631,789055976,2823,2231369728,39,'Myridian Sun (4)',0,41,6,-2585,-7428,'As a member of PoR, I remember the DoL vs HC/PoR wars well.  DoL always had the preponderance of spheres and active dreamers.  Where as HC had pure numbers (during wartime).  It often fell upon PoR to battle DoL in skirmishes to keep DoL off balence until HC arrived to aid.  Quite often it was PoR that tipped the balence one way or another (especially once our own spheres attained the 3rd sphere range).    I am particularly fond of one such skirmish, in which CoRrUpTiOn, thornack, and myself managed...','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2087599,789055976,2825,2231369728,39,'Myridian Sun (3)',0,41,6,-2596,-7420,'I soon joined the Protectors.  Even in my early dreams I tended to focus on the house rather than myself (much to the anoyance of my teacher and future wife).  Saving of souls, aiding newly awakened, these were the driving forces of my dreams.  Defeating the Darks my main goal even to this day.   3 months into the war against the Darks, I was knighted for my role in helping to re-organize our forces.  Making Little PoR a rather dismal place for the Darks to attack.  Even without a keep of our own. ','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2087694,789055976,2822,2231369728,39,'Myridian Sun (5)',0,41,6,-2573,-7436,'To take the keep by making the jump on our first attempt as we rushed the keep. catching flushy un free actioned certainly helped in this matter.  we held the keep for 2 full hours until HC arrived, then we proceeded to smash Valourin\'s Forces and hold their house for an hour.  (DoL had done this to us in GGE not two days before with the  same results. as such it felt good to get our own back as it were).  But while those times were exciting.  I am most proud of the temporary alliances I was able...','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2087726,789055976,2820,2231369728,39,'Myridian Sun (6)',0,41,6,-2564,-7445,'to hamer out with DoL, HC, PoR, UoTC to combat the Darks.  Any \"shots in the back\" were dealt with harshly by all to maintain the strength against the darks.  for over 2 years these held in place. until the houses fell... *the ink seems to pool for a bit as if the pen was held steady...* Iden... *the name appears written with a Flourish of anger*  ','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(12718264,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,23,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:01'),(12718263,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,23,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:01'),(12718262,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,23,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:01'),(10385365,53381,13437953,0,0,'Tears',0,26,2,132,-3522,'','2016-11-05 04:54:11'),(10385545,526867,1642594561,115201,2615296,'Ward',0,26,2,231,-4206,'','2016-11-05 05:20:44'),(10385367,53381,13437953,0,0,'Tears',0,26,2,393,-3524,'','2016-11-05 04:55:21'),(7989723,134744548,3070,4261412864,41,'SoulShield',0,41,5,504,-6250,'The History of Soul Shield can be found on the Chaos Scrolls.  See the index for \"Arts\".  A copy had been inscribed and placed here by Shoury, but had to be removed due to space limitations.\r\n','2016-01-10 02:37:34'),(2117591,789055972,3070,2231369728,39,'Fires Glow (3)',0,41,11,-5651,-2388,'A splash is heard and felt as the refugee\'s splash into the evernight lake in surprise. They had not known of its existance... no one had come this far into the darkened plan, not even the clans themselves...  making their way to the far side they stop as one as the matriarch raises her hand. the sounds of pursuit have stopped.  As a group everyone flinches, from ahead they hear soft growls. Terror begins to sink even further into their bones as the ragged band huddles together on the edges of that shore..','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2117606,789055972,3070,2231369728,39,'Fires Glow (4)',0,41,11,-5659,-2377,'Dim images can be seen on the far side of the lake... where the moons light has escaped the cloud covering, and fall upon hideous beasts.  The pathetic group desperatly surrounds its women with anyone old enough to see lightening and hear thunder... crude impliments readied in defense.  ','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2117638,789055972,3070,2231369728,39,'Fires Glow (5)',0,41,11,-5665,-2361,'The patriarch steps through the crowd, brushing off the few hands that dare reach out to stop her.  Whispers of her nature spread though the group.  She is the matriarch, strongest of them.  Most intune with the elements.  Never has her power been manifest however. She wades through the waters towards the beasts, gasps are heard as the lakes waters seem to roil around her, steam fills the air.  She reaches the other side, a faint glow can be seen through the mists she created. Suddenly a roar goes up...','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2117670,789055972,3070,2231369728,39,'Fires Glow (6)',0,41,11,-5660,-2350,'The host rushes towards her...cries of dismay sweep the refugee\'s... then shouts of pain as the lake reflects the sudden bloom of a roaring fire!  their eyes cannot adjust to the brilliance... the beasts howl in agony. some actually on fire! they rush from the area their terror heard long into the night as they flee onward. The mists slowly part and clear. But where is the matriarch? Cautiously, tools raised in defense, the refugees move towards the light. Where she last stood, now lay a fire. ','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2117702,789055972,3070,2231369728,39,'Fires Glow (7)',0,41,11,-5639,-2416,'No fuel is seen, only a fire springing forth from the ground.  And no matriarch to be seen. The fire seems to sing with an eternal laughter.  It\'s warmth spreads through the room, showing a beautiful lake, its edges covered in lillies and various plants. Small echoes of her words seem to drift on the warm air.  \"Rest, Sleep, live my people, my glow shall protect you, warm you, keep you, My light will drive them from you.. \" ~Myridian Sun -Evernight Lake','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(7394582,5877,13438207,0,0,'Portal Conduit',0,18,7,7669,4985,'A large rod constructed of an unknown polished metal.  Elementricity courses through it and forms a ring with any other nearby portal conduits.  ','2015-10-23 00:42:46'),(2128984,65657,989856275,0,0,'Wish Needle',0,22,22,-10126,-7287,'The needle appears simple but emits a soft glow, when a string is placed near it, the string will fit its way thru the needles opening, and glow right along with it.  The needle will sew, build and and repair even the toughest fabrics.  Giving its bearer, the completed results that they \'wish\'.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(12577497,872679432,50397967,10752,0,'Jade Gold Charm',0,39,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-07 17:44:31'),(12718261,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,23,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:01'),(12577495,285345984,235800577,6,0,'Blood Shield',0,39,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-07 17:44:31'),(12718260,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,23,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:01'),(10205688,5717,13437953,0,0,'Undergames Crystal',0,43,7,9790,-5191,'','2016-10-14 02:36:05'),(2191070,1711802852,3070,1627389952,41,'Staff of Resilience',0,41,5,629,-6619,'In the dreams of old, each focus had a Prime Artifact. The one of the SoulMasters was the Staff of Resilience. I, along with many other Masters searched and found pieces of said Staff. They were fused back together and the Staff made whole. Last known dreamer to hold the Staff of Resilience was Rathis Tarn. ~c','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2200337,1711802852,3070,1627389952,41,'Who Am I ? ~ 3',0,41,6,-2496,-7832,'As you may have guessed, this can be a very lonely existence..although nothing quite compares to helping to bring new life into the world, I must admit I do often find myself pining...to be like the families that I serve...which is how I imagine I came to my dreams here....continued....','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2200302,1711802852,3070,1627389952,41,'Who Am I ? ~ 1',0,41,6,-2478,-7805,'I am Cianne Andrea McCleoud, born to Angus & Lillian McCleoud. I hail from a village called Dunlain, a magical land of immense beauty, the flora and fauna captivate, the eastern shore is mesmerising and to the west, the raw beauty of a mountain range...','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2200304,1711802852,3070,1627389952,41,'Who Am I ? ~ 2',0,41,6,-2487,-7819,'In my village and surrounding areas, I am a midwife, Those formally trained in medicine are few and far between. I have never married, and so am able to travel for days on end when I am needed. Many times, I will stay with an expectant mother in her last weeks, and do not return until after the child is born and it is certain that the new mother is able to care for it on her own....continued...','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(12718259,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,23,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:01'),(2710099,526820,3070,721420288,39,'Cadilin\'s 2/2',0,41,11,-5813,-2089,'Cadilin\'s Charm Hill - Lambent Flat: ...that it was too late and that Calidin had already had his way with his daughter. In a violent rage the father slew Cadilin, Cadilin was burried on the Hill and it was named after him and the charm that sedcued so many women and was the cause of his death.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2611317,267925,3893694209,16770048,0,'Fractal',0,33,15,11932,186,'','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2297520,117967332,3070,1627389952,41,'Pride & Joy',0,41,14,5734,-2086,'A large oil on canvas depicts A stunning woman with shining silver white hair, piled loosely, a few delicate tendrils of curls frame her exquisite face. Delicate pointed ears are exposed. Eyes of stunning violet. She wears a\r\n cobalt blue toga, deep as the night sky, cinched at the waist with filigreed silver webbing. It flutters in a light breeze. An ornate runed Khopesh is at her side. An emerald halo glows above her head. She is standing in a pumpkin patch. A  delicious smirk is on her face. ','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(12719290,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,49,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:27'),(2425869,4010281444,3070,2130706432,39,'Roland 1/2',0,41,6,-2446,-7601,'Ruler of the old Order, brother of Amygdala, husband of Gwenivere. An astute and political man known for his ability to roll his eyes at a chak fight while poking at an agoknight essence with a ruler in front of a class full of knowledge hungry students. In his later dreams..','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(12719378,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,51,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:29'),(2521751,4144499172,3070,2130706432,39,'RIP Ishido',0,41,6,-2526,-7764,'RIP my friend, you\'ll never ever be forgotten and you\'ll never ever leave our hearts. Love you dearly & forever! ','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2425871,4010281444,3070,2130706432,39,'Roland 2/2',0,41,6,-2436,-7620,'..he was a bit more crotchety and therefore less focused on his studies. He was certainly more willing to pick up a chak and also willing to join a war to fight alongside an allied friend. He was a good man and an even better friend.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2472051,1057491428,3070,3456106496,41,'Mare List~ 6/26',0,41,4,3554,-4875,'Darks: Foulmouth, Kruugaar, lvunsasu, Yaza\'s (shapeshifters) ...Days: Bhegwir, Baruk, Korg, Radak, Fakar, Cigar, Sak, Pink, Sugdush, Kink, viiriis, and many others. They can change over quickly. ~Updated 6/26','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2485222,1862797796,3070,721420288,39,'Combine History 1/2',0,41,5,-254,-6981,'Ibioc was a great Master that worked diligently on Recharge.His knowledge of talisman was unrivalled. Like many of the Great Smiths, he too studied at one time under the Srechethan Kabal. The art of combine was already old when Ibioc discovered Recharge. He knew how natural and easy Combine is compared to Recharge in many respects. Ibioc wanted to do more than just fuse talisman together...He sought to dig deeper into an item & increase its power. His oath to the Guild prevented him from revealing Combine.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2504972,4043835876,3070,1308622848,39,'Avatar to Arts 1',0,41,17,-6865,-88,'I believe that upon entering the dreamstate, our raw subconscience borrows the energy required to form an avatar from the City itself. Through this we take what energy is required to sustain us in a somewhat physical form. This shell is our protection, and one of our greatest tools. The avatar serves many purposes such as shielding our subconscience (soul essence), providing us with a physical sensation in a plane of existence foreign to our native shards, and as a tool to accomplish our goals....','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2505035,4043835876,3070,1308622848,39,'Avatar to Arts 2',0,41,17,-6876,-103,'Evocation, is when we are drawing from within our avatars the required energy needed and manipulating it to complete the intended art evoke. A firm belief of mine is that we are very much connected to this City as dreamers. The energy we borrow is broken down to its original raw form and distributed back into the City when we wake. I believe if it did not our empty avatars would be stuck in place after we wake, and those in the City would be able to see our mindless, empty shells.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2505130,4043835876,3070,1308622848,39,'Draining 2',0,41,2,1359,-4001,'It is a well known fact that energy cannot be destroyed, so as you\'re hitting someone with your blade or chakram you are, in essence, causing the draining of their energy to the point where their avatar breaks and its energies returned to the City. Restore, grants you your avatar back through simulating the act of entering the dreamstate, that initial drain that gives you form. Everything must get its energy from somwhere else. Dreaming -is- draining... Over the inevitable, thou shouldst not grieve...','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2505162,4043835876,3070,1308622848,39,'Draining 1',0,41,2,1353,-3989,'When entering the dreamstate, we borrow energy from the City to give us the form of our avatars. To borrow this energy, we must naturally drain it from the source. When we wake, the energy is returned to its source in its original, raw state. To understand Draining and its harmless benefits, one much understand that we are draining energy in everything that we do. Art evokes are the result of draining energy from your avatar to manipulate it towards the intended outcome.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2521747,4144499172,3070,2130706432,39,'Ishido 1/2',0,41,6,-2485,-7735,'Early in his dreams Ishido was rumored to have been an initiate of DoL. When I came to know him he was a mouthy freespirit whom often voiced hard opinions against the houses and how they were run. He wasn\'t afraid of anyone and made sure to give his piece','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2521750,4144499172,3070,2130706432,39,'Ishido 2/2',0,41,6,-2506,-7746,'of mind whether asked or not. He was a mentor to a good part of the Lyran dreamers and was a pillar in the freespirit community. Loyalty to his closest friends was unwavering. His influence on the Dream still resonates through our halls to this day.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2596805,1997015524,3070,3607101440,41,'LadySilver',0,21,16,-2763,-3071,'LadySilver dropped a pin, it was very quiet, I have stolen it. She noticed yet laughed and introduced herself. She is a silly Seer, I shall have fun.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2710067,526820,3070,721420288,39,'Cadilin\'s 1/2',0,41,11,-5814,-2128,'Cadilin\'s Charm Hill; Lambent Flats: By Aileron. Back In the older dreams there was a man named Cadilin, he was considered a handsome man by the ladies and a typical flirt. He would take the ladies to the Hill use his suave and charming mannor to get close to them then make his move. One day he took a beautiful young lady to the hill and seduced her. The brother of this girl heard about Cadilin and told his father that she went with him. Enraged the father went to the hill to find ...','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2673026,3876063716,3070,4160749568,39,'New FS Art List (1)',0,41,20,3829,1006,'\r\nMirage: Create a mirror image of yourself in your current position.\r\nRebound: Chakrams bounce off a percentage of the time.\r\nExtrasensory: Sense when you are located.\r\nLoudmouth: Effected dreamer can be heard in all adjacent rooms when talking or shouting, and cannot whisper. Replaces Silence if in effect.\r\nSilence: Effected dreamer can only whisper, not speak or shout. Replaces Loudmouth if in effect.\r\nButterfingers: Target dreamer (push distance) drops their currently held item. ','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2673058,3876063716,3070,4160749568,39,'New FS Art List (2)',0,41,20,3811,1006,'\r\nVentriloquism: Speak with another dreamer\'s voice (whisper distance?), perhaps limited by pregenerated phrases?\r\nNearsight: Effected dreamer\'s targeting arts now require line-of-sight.\r\nScramble: Target dreamer (push distance) has items moved around randomly in their inventory.\r\nHallucinate: Creates a hallucination token of chosen Dreamer(A); Using the token targets an individual dreamer(B) in line of sight. Targetted dreamer(B) can now see dreamer(A) moving in semi-random patterns around the room. \r\n','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2673184,3876063716,3070,4160749568,39,'FS Art Details (2)',0,41,20,3759,1010,'\r\nOrbit 40: Rebound (1 min + 1 per plateau, no stacking duration. 3% success + 3% per plateau) Cost: 20 Lucidity\r\nOrbit 45: Mirage (3min +3 min per plateau, only one mirage at a time. Vision shows Mirage name.) Cost: 20 Lucidity\r\nOrbit 55: Hallucinate (3min + 3 per plateau, only one hallucination token can be created at a time. Vision shows Hallucination name) Cost: 25 Lucidity\r\nOrbit 60: Nearsight (10 secs + 10 per plateau; evoke speed long) Cost: 30 Lucidity\r\n','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2684617,526820,3070,318767104,39,'Codex',0,47,7,2587,4334,'**Plateau tasks should increase in difficulty as the plateau increases. Ex. Free Action to 80 should be incredibly more difficult that a Free Action to 10.\r\n**A Teacher may not give a Plateau task for a Minor Art until the student has reached the next Sphere. (EX. A GateKeeper learns Identify at 30 and would not be able to plateau ID to 10 until Orbit 40. They would also not be able to plateau the art to 20 until Orbit 50)\r\n**A Teacher, if found to be violating or abusing the Teaching System, may have thei','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2684616,526820,3070,318767104,39,'Codex',0,47,7,2572,4349,'E. Tasking and Plateauing\r\n** A Student may only have one active task from the same Teacher at a time. They may have multiple tasks from multiple teachers. Exceptions to this rule are tasks for Forge, Train or Sphere.\r\n**A Student may report a task as soon as they are ready. If the Student can report sooner than one dream cycle, then the task difficulty should be adjusted.\r\n**A Teacher may decide the difficulty of a “To Learn” task. It should challenge the Student but not be so difficult that it takes th','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2700218,4261939684,3070,637534208,39,'Reweave: History',0,41,5,541,-6940,'Reweave was created by the DreamWright Mantic, as part of the Forger\'s Circle. He was very concerned with rebuilding and creating things. In particular, he searched for an art that would help strengthen the City walls. His first attempt at this was the art of reweave. Naturally, it was too weak. Even at higher plateaus it could not affect the walls on a large scale, but could be used as spot repair. After experimentation, he found that he could strengthen the durability of shields.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2721662,2215119332,1510398,3892314112,2578473,'Forge 70 Jerulan',0,41,23,-3819,1892,'Obtain a soul essence!  Use the soul essence and forge something spectacular!  Invite the city and get help from as many forgers as you can!  I\'m sure you\'ll do great and your efforts will be worth a 70 plateau!  I know you can do it!  ','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2760273,906496488,5376816,3456106496,2565673,'Vamp40~ Blade',0,47,9,-4763,4097,'While combing through my many books, I\'ve come across mentions of old artifacts. I would like for you to do your own research, and find one that would be beneficial to the SM guild. Bring up the history, and how it can be brought to the group. Involve as many as you can~','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(3130066,526820,3070,822083584,41,'Mortar and Pestle',0,41,14,5771,-2035,'A small ivory bowl, with stains of residue discoloring the white on the inside. Propped within is a heavy blunt, club-shaped object that appears to be a sanded down tusk. Braided yarn is looped around the top for a comfortable grip.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2929822,526820,3070,1107296256,39,'Changes - Arts',0,41,19,-4308,-484,'Missing arts are missing, it would appear, and many have been gained. In this City, you have access to minor arts that were previous not available, such as Free Action for a Dreamseer. These arts cannot be plateau\'d above 29. Additionally, your energy arts do not exist in this City, as the nightmare essences have filled the gap Energy Spheres once covered. The bartering ability of energy is gone, as well. Yes, unfortunately, you will no longer be able to improve shields or chakrams without Forge, 50+ art.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2929857,526820,3070,1107296256,39,'Changes - City 2',0,41,19,-4307,-483,'...to manipulation by dreamers, whether in the form of energy manipulation or brute force and construction. While it may be considered a negative, the loss of these abilities has translated into a City that appears much more stable at its foundation, though the Idaoclesian tenants of creativity and innovation are still welcome, and needed.\r\n','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2929790,526820,3070,1107296256,39,'Changes - Beasts',0,41,19,-4286,-476,'There are two major changes to beasts. First, there are lesser nightmares roaming around which you have likely encountered. Emphants are the easiest, then Bogroms, Agoknight, Shamblix and Horrons. Horrons and Shamblix are similar to the Hotaii in that they paralyze you with gaze or shot, and are very strong. The second is they are called mares, and that there are \"Daymares\" which are lesser versions of the Hotaii with no frontal immunity, however some arts such as Blast require the back.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2929858,526820,3070,1107296256,39,'Changes - Beliefs',0,41,19,-4312,-481,'The most common change in the City is the belief system. Some Lyrans believe every mare has a soul, and that improper treatment of that soul destroys the potential dreamer\'s ability to dream. The mistreatment of those souls is a common cause to war, given the grave nature and theoretically mass genocide committed by either party. Additionally, some believe that the treatment of those essences can simply harm the City itself by causing imbalance to chaotic energy, similarly reducing the City\'s population.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(3252171,1124600292,1969150,452984832,2565674,'Poison 60 - Blade',0,47,9,-4821,4096,'Take steps to eliminate the Consortium\'s lingering grip on the City. This can be pursued in any way you see fit, but ensure instant or lingering damage to them.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(3251817,2835421049,1062,0,0,'MT Requirements',0,22,22,-10182,-6379,'Attention young Citizens. The following are the new requirements for the station of Master Teacher. *Train to 50  *8 arts to 50 (Major, minor and dreamsoul combination)  *3 arts to 40 (Major, minor and Dreamsoul combination)  *3 supports from fellow teachers. Your past tasking will weigh heavily on consideration. Once raised to the station, you will be expected to use Train Self to improve your remaining art levels. Failure to improve your arts can be grounds for removal from the MT Council.  **A**\r\n','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(3251883,2835421049,1070,0,0,'MT Requirements',0,18,2,-826,1879,'Attention young Citizens. The following are the new requirements for the station of Master Teacher. *Train 50  *8 arts to 50 (Major,minor and Dreamsoul combination)  *3 arts to 40 (Major, minor and Dreamsoul combination)  *3 supports from fellow teachers. Your past tasking will weigh heavily on consideration. Once raised to the station, you will be expected to use Train Self to improve your remaining art levles. Failure to improve your arts can be grounds for removal from the MT Council. **A**','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2986068,1862797796,3070,1627389952,41,'~ Deluge~',0,41,11,-6970,-2277,'Where do we go from here...\r\nfragmented thoughts like a prism of colors -\r\nbouncing off too many walls...\r\na single teardrop in an ocean of memories, \r\nwashed away by the swiftly approaching tide....\r\nwhere do you find light in the deluge of icy darkness that closes in...\r\nstealing your breath until you suffocate........','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(3104916,134744552,199467,2063597568,2579751,'Dreamseer 60',0,18,31,15557,-5266,'Now is a great time to gather some Dreamseer battle tendancies. I want you to observe some of the tactics of the other Dreamseers we are at war with.  What sort of tactics are they using?  Which ones are willing to get down and dirty with chaks and which will sit on a wall and blast?  I also want you to find the best locations to hunt where we can draw them into an attack.  See if you can somehow gather them into a trap at the keep or somewhere else.  Find a way to make their tactics work to our advantage.','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2986005,1611139556,3070,1627389952,41,'A Different Dream 3',0,41,11,-7023,-2306,'My thoughts are fragmented like the colors of a prism that bounce off too many walls at the same time. A single tear drop in an ocean of memories...where is the light to be found in the deluge of icy darkness that steals your breath away.....','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2986069,1862797796,3070,1627389952,41,'~ Deluge ~',0,41,11,-6978,-2295,'Where do we go from here...\r\nfragmented thoughts like a prism of colors -\r\nbouncing off too many walls...\r\na single teardrop in an ocean of memories, \r\nwashed away by the swiftly approaching tide....\r\nwhere do you find light in the deluge of icy darkness that closes in...\r\nstealing your breath until you suffocate........','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(2985506,3775400420,3070,1627389952,41,'True Clarity',0,17,30,12077,-8694,'A life sized canvas depicts a stunning woman, small in stature, radiating strength and confidence. Wearing a snug leather bustier underneath a simple tunic that drapes softly to mid thigh. Feminine yet sturdy leather boots adorn her feet.  A diamond ring on her left hand sparkles brilliantly. A  faint grin on her lips, lustrous sandy, silver locks cut into a sexy bob. Melancholy eyes of the deepest evernight sky grip your heart... She looks back over her shoulder..her eyes ever watching, always on guard..','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(3014096,262233,1023,10241,0,'GK Practice Blade',0,39,11,10376,5279,'','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(3014098,151257177,1023,10241,0,'SM Practice Blade',0,39,11,10274,5310,'','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(12717730,637601928,570557452,0,0,'Cyan Fire Alteror',0,10,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:17:48'),(12717731,1140918408,134480913,0,0,'Jade Alteror',0,10,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:17:48'),(12717732,50399176,318833169,0,0,'Gold Chalk Elemen',0,10,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:17:48'),(12717733,3758163912,822084113,0,0,'Chalk Earth Elemen',0,10,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:17:48'),(7793410,3992980469,13437953,0,0,'Staff of Earth',0,23,4,366,-8231,'A large staff carved completely out of stone.  It\'s shaft is covered with etched symbols that emit a white glow.','2015-12-15 01:51:29'),(12719377,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,51,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:29'),(12719376,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,51,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:29'),(12719375,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,51,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:29'),(3252203,4261939684,4656126,637534208,2561831,'Dina: Flame 60',0,47,9,-4766,3504,'I would like for you to create a physical representation of your flame. A monument of sorts, out within the City. It should embody your FlameSear and be easily recognizable for what it is to anyone else. Involve as many others as you can, SoulMaster or not... SoulMasters would likely be the most helpful though.\r\n','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(3218805,940050920,9505583,2063597568,2562087,'Chaos Well 20 ',0,47,6,-3619,5644,'There are a couple things that are peculiar with Chaos Wells as items that make them unique.  I\'d like you to investigate what these are.  Further to this, how are they tied to our appearance? Why do they mimic our outer appearance?\r\n','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(7358266,117702777,150995967,10246,0,'Cognizant Talon',0,17,25,-521,-12000,'A narrow, one-foot long blade with both edges sharpened to a deadly degree. The hilt is carved with runes within its peculiar metal that suggests an incantation. It shines in the light, yet is also easy to conceal. In the hilt is a stone that bristles with energy. Peering at it for too long gives an impression of repulsion or dread.','2015-10-18 02:54:41'),(3251815,2835421049,1072,0,0,'MT Requirements',0,25,7,-3855,2669,'Attention young CItizens. The following are the new requirements for the station on Master Teacher.  *Train 50  *8 arts to 50 (Major, mino and Dreamsoul combination)  * 3 arts to 40 (Major, minor and Dreamsoul combination)  *3 supports from fellow teachers. Your past tasking will weigh heavily on consideration. Once raised to the station, you will be expected to use Train Self to improve your remaining art levels. Failure to improve your arts can be grounds for removal from the MT Council.  **A**\r\n','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(3251816,2835421049,1072,0,0,'MT Requirements',0,17,30,12532,-9903,'Attention young Citizens. The following are the new requirements for the station of Master Teacher.  *Train of 50  *8 arts at 50 (Major, minor and Dreamsoul combination)  *3 arts at 40 (Major, minor and Dreamsoul combination)  *3 supports from fellow teachers. Your past tasking will weigh heavily on consideration. Once raised to the station, you will be expected to use Train Self to improve your remaining art levels. Failure to improve your arts can be grounds for removal from the MT Council.  **A**\r\n','2015-10-10 16:27:44'),(7793444,50334069,13437953,0,0,'1 or L',0,23,2,594,-2861,'A square stone tablet.  In the middle of the tablet is a large engraving of the letter: \"L\" or if turned upside down the number \"1\"','2015-12-15 01:58:31'),(7356749,262521,419693567,10754,0,'Srechethan\'s Heart',0,18,8,8261,2428,'A large ruby pendant hangs from a white chromium chain.  The ruby is cut into a faceted oval about the size of a man\'s fist.  A glowing crimson light pulses off and on dimly inside the ruby, almost like a heartbeat.','2015-10-17 21:45:32'),(12719374,0,0,0,0,'level item',0,51,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:18:29'),(7371209,526820,3070,570425344,39,'Catacombs',0,47,6,-3619,5644,'Forward: Down stairs, turn right, R, F until 2nd L, L, R, R, L, 2nd L, L, 2nd R, R, L, L, R, L, R, S, L.                                                           Backwards: Look at portal, turn L down stairs. R, L, R, 2nd L, R, R, L, L, R, 2nd R, L, L, R, S, L.','2015-10-19 23:07:07'),(7394579,5877,13438207,0,0,'Portal Conduit',0,18,9,8548,-1661,'A large rod constructed of an unknown polished metal.  Elementricity courses through it and forms a ring with any other nearby portal conduits.  ','2015-10-23 00:42:02'),(7394580,5877,13438207,0,0,'Portal Conduit',0,18,9,8672,-1177,'A large rod constructed of an unknown polished metal.  Elementricity courses through it and forms a ring with any other nearby portal conduits.  ','2015-10-23 00:42:19'),(7394691,520096629,13437953,0,0,'Sealed Box',0,18,9,8434,-1659,'A small box made of strong steel.  The symbol of the Valley stronghold house is on the lid.  The lid has been sealed shut.','2015-10-23 01:09:39'),(7394581,5877,13438207,0,0,'Portal Conduit',0,18,7,8524,5953,'A large rod constructed of an unknown polished metal.  Elementricity courses through it and forms a ring with any other nearby portal conduits.  ','2015-10-23 00:42:33'),(7394616,4629,13437953,0,0,'PoR Flag',0,18,26,8082,-17675,'','2015-10-23 00:53:06'),(7394615,4629,13437953,0,0,'PoR Flag',0,18,26,8438,-17740,'','2015-10-23 00:52:44'),(7394688,71481,102565119,0,0,'Siren\'s Voice',0,18,8,8323,2162,'A large silver spider about 8 inches wide.  The spider\'s legs are able to open or close when the spider\'s head is pressed.  The body of the spider is made of solid jade.','2015-10-23 01:04:04'),(10385481,526867,2749890817,104961,2615296,'Ward',0,26,2,-655,-3326,'','2016-11-05 05:20:34'),(7417030,4533,13437953,0,0,'KoES Flag',0,18,8,8640,2302,'A flag of the Keepers of the Eternal Shadows.  The banner has clear claw marks and it\'s bottom is shredded.','2015-10-25 23:24:25'),(7453630,1325926884,3070,452984832,39,'Museum',0,47,6,-2106,4897,'Relics here will be moved to the museum after a proper presentation.','2015-10-30 21:44:22'),(7613993,101190116,3070,3523215360,40,'Tome of Keilara',0,47,9,-4890,4153,'This tome, inscribed by myself, Keilara, is to inform each sphering teacher that BladeSlayer is on his dual focus journey and is excused from any and all sphere tasking. If you have any concerns, seek out any Elder Teacher at your leisure.','2015-11-21 06:29:07'),(10077171,3876063716,3070,4160749568,39,'Pulling Arts - 1',0,47,6,-3437,6327,'\r\n1.) Lure; Dreamsoul; Orbit 55; Cost: 20 Dreamsoul\r\nEffect: Sacrifice one talisman, and all generators on the same plane as you will be more likely to produce that type (and strength) of talisman for a number of minutes equal to the charges of the destroyed talisman. \r\n\r\n2.) Summons; Dreamsoul; Orbit 30; Cost: 5 Dreamsoul\r\nEffect: Select a dreamer as with Locate Dreamer. If on same plane, they are informed that you seek their presence. Only works on Dreamers of lower sphere, or lower rank (same house). ','2016-09-27 20:07:27'),(12717664,822216896,471599105,8,0,'Blood Gold Shield',0,8,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:17:46'),(7605883,134744548,3070,2063597568,39,'Judgement History 1',0,41,5,147,-6969,'Judgement was created by the dreamer Kaylar.  A justice of the city court, Kaylar presided over many cases of varying degree, seeing all manner of innocense and vile behavior brought before him.  One thing irked him in particuar, however. Unless the dreamer was notorious, or a braggart, the more canny evildoers could disguise their sphere symbols not allowing him to make a suitable punishment or penalty.  Some would pretend to be higher sphere, in hopes of being let off.','2015-11-20 02:42:36'),(12717663,3154184136,855900684,0,0,'Beige Sand Elemen',0,8,0,0,0,NULL,'2017-09-28 17:17:46'),(8356956,3876063716,3070,4160749568,39,'Patternization',0,41,20,3664,1004,'Condensing the creation of the lucidic plates, and their targetting thereof, will need to occur into a talisman -- Compendium? When the Compendium of the pattern is designed, it will need to be protected from outer influences; I\'ll need a book case to protect it. Metal? How do I prevent outside influences? What are potential problem influences? ','2016-02-26 09:34:57'),(7605930,134744548,3070,2063597568,39,'Judgement History 3',0,41,5,129,-6970,'They would state their sphere something it was not, only to have it shamefacedly revealed, exposing their lies.  - Thank you to Palani for the research.','2015-11-20 02:46:49'),(7605925,134744548,3070,2063597568,39,'Judgement History 2',0,41,5,147,-6969,'Other dreamers would choose to say they were a lower sphere in the hopes of being offered a more lenient sentance.  So after much consideration and discussion with his colleagues, Kaylar formed a very peircing art of Insight, that would examine the relative strength of a dreamer.  Being an avid duelist, Kaylar also tweaked it to show the general health of the dreamer as an added benefit.  It is said that his court was quite amusing for a while as those who were unaware of the art would lie to Kaylar.','2015-11-20 02:45:35'),(7606309,134744552,2856,2063597568,39,'Top 5 Annoyances 5',0,41,4,3926,-5418,'Dreaming every night for two weeks and seeing the odd passing dreamer, then learning that the one night you did not dream, 30 dreamers were all in the same room and the walls were pulled off of a house to rennovate it.\r\n','2015-11-20 03:55:39'),(7606277,134744552,2857,2063597568,39,'Top 5 Annoyances 4',0,41,4,3919,-5429,'As a teacher, handing out a task to a dreamer and them accepting it.  Months and months pass and that student returns to you and asks for a new one, meaning it was either pitched off a cliff or just sat unactivated in a pack.','2015-11-20 03:51:15'),(7606243,134744552,2857,2063597568,39,'Top 5 Annoyances 2',0,41,4,3899,-5451,'Receiving a task after waiting 20 minutes for it to be inscribed in quest.  Then accepting that quest and the teacher wakes and you suddenly realize that the quest has been tagged to another dreamer and you accepted not paying attention.','2015-11-20 03:44:26'),(7606241,134744552,2854,2063597568,39,'Top 5  Annoyances 1',0,41,4,3888,-5460,'Walking into a room to report to a teacher only to see him or her explode into a plume of white smoke as soon as you enter into it.\r\n','2015-11-20 03:41:55'),(7606276,134744552,2861,2063597568,39,'Top 5 Annoyances 3',0,41,4,3910,-5440,'Sitting at a Gen for hours, finding items for every other focus.  Then, finally, a chakram appears for your own focus and it\'s great.  So you take it to a DreamSeer to have it recharged and it explodes on the first evoke.\r\n','2015-11-20 03:46:31'),(8104315,1140856917,13437953,0,0,'Ceremony Flag',0,22,22,-10034,-6418,'','2016-01-25 03:29:07'),(7726461,2198342116,3070,4261412864,41,'Dina\'s Bodyless 2',0,41,18,-8485,-409,'Dina was given the box as something that was found inside the house.  Dina opened it and found a button inside, that when pressed.... stripped her of her avatar.  The box itself was a negative ten to ninty-nine dreamsoul talisman.  There have been two attempts that I know of to restore Dina\'s avatar, both failures.\r\n','2015-12-06 01:59:44'),(8136788,134744552,3345192,2063597568,2639655,'NMF 10 - Flower',0,47,6,-3509,5862,'I want you to think of a theoretical way of evoking a mass-NMF art on a roomful of dreamer.  I\'d also like you to somehow limit their vocabulary to the same as a Datoken.  As a fatesender, how do you think you could use this art for maximum evil, assuming the art could not be reflected and there was no immunity to anyone in the room.','2016-01-29 03:52:18'),(7636021,855638325,13437953,0,0,'Golden Skeleton Key',0,18,12,-7259,1680,'This appears to be an old-fashioned skeleton key. It vibrates with willpower and sparkles with flecks of gold. It emits a steady humming sound.','2015-11-24 05:07:18'),(7635813,4144499172,3070,1107296256,39,'Metal plaque',0,41,10,-2297,-9433,'Augh Essul, depicted above, was the first Forger of the Idaoclesian City. We did not even have the words Forge Talisman, or Forge associated with what he was doing, we simply called what he was doing as crafting, or smithing. While he never formally introduced us to Forge, what he did do was challenge our creativity, showing us that creation was possible within in the City of Dreams for those who sought to master it, as was anything our creativity conjured up.','2015-11-24 04:20:31'),(7635737,4144499172,3070,1107296256,39,'Metal plaque',0,41,10,-2298,-9448,'Bashir was an ancient dreamer who ascended to a higher form. After its ascension, it was hunted by the Yissen, who sought to bring its power into check, as Bashir habitually terrorized dreamers, calling itself a God. While the being\'s true form is unknown, it frequented the four forms above,  wrecking havoc to all who opposed it. It inspired the Cult of Bashir, who offering blood offerings to the diety in exchange for power. When it was destroyed, Shards of Bashir populated the City, now known to be Mares.','2015-11-24 04:05:47'),(7633527,4144499172,3070,1107296256,39,'Metal Plaque',0,41,10,-2299,-9418,'Depicted here is A\'kmar Ralnora, Third Soulmaster and Initiate of Sect of the Prudent. He was first of two Variant Walkers in the Idaoclesian City, revealing to dreamers that other cities existed, and the small community we were surrounded by was simply a fraction of potential dreamers within our midst. He was slain by Ra\'as, empowered by Bashir of the Cult, in defense of his housemates, at Path of Justice, Edgeward Barrows.','2015-11-23 20:33:00'),(7636442,68601,16974587,0,0,'Scepter of Souls',0,18,8,8280,2050,'A short rod of limestone stalactite, nearing two feet in length. The shaft is sanded down to a smooth finish, with grooves spiraling downward. Initials and personal markings are carved into the base. Affixed at the top is a blown glass shrine; the swirled purple hues creates a vortex effect with the clear liquid it contains. The Scepter becomes engulfed in an abyssal shroud when wielded by a SoulMaster.','2015-11-24 06:24:46'),(7696127,2466254069,13437966,0,0,'Soul Fragment',0,11,17,-12248,-3697,'A circular shaped object, with flecks of gold and pink contained within. It appears to have been cracked from something.','2015-12-02 04:49:29'),(7680917,956304629,13437957,0,0,'Soul Fragment',0,18,8,8407,2250,'A misshapen object that appears to have been shattered from something else; it glows with flecks of pink and gold and has a neutral energy emitting from it. ','2015-11-30 05:33:06'),(9574905,2130774521,3254780671,0,0,'Immortal Dreams VI',0,2,31,10251,-10210,'A torn codex page, the edged singed. Upon the page are numerous glowing runes, a faint blue light emitted from it. Three holes at the top of the page, iron rings placed into them.','2016-07-28 08:28:54'),(7680097,1996750969,402654092,10246,0,'Warden\'s Dagger',0,18,10,-3982,1524,'A six inch blade comprised of a shard of obsidian glass with Abyss, Berry, Jade, and Gold metals swirled around it. Small \"Y\" symbols have been into the blade every inch and emit a soft pulsating glow when held in an offensive posture. The crossguard has a phoenix with a single tear of fire etched into the center. The Night hilt gives off a light Cyan glow whenever the light hits it at a 45 degree angle. The pommel of the hilt has a small \"-¥-\" etched into either side.','2015-11-30 02:34:53'),(7726460,2198342116,3070,4261412864,41,'Dina\'s Bodyless 1',0,41,18,-8475,-414,'Dina\'s current situation came about as the result of maneuverings from Lothrick and Lu Chaos (At the time, Consortium).  Lothrick had Lu Chaos arrange to place the \"Ancient Box\" that caused Dina to lose her avatar, inside the halls of the Order.  I have not been able to confirm which of the dreamers, either Lucille, Dar\'canon, or Cuero actuall placed the item, but it was one of those three.\r\n','2015-12-06 01:57:34'),(7715168,855902329,263167,10753,0,'Practice GK Chakram',0,39,11,10381,5255,'Please leave me in the Arena!','2015-12-04 16:52:08'),(7715133,4278454393,263167,10753,0,'Practice FS Chakram',0,39,11,10475,5254,'Please leave me in the Arena!','2015-12-04 16:47:02'),(7715173,3137603705,263167,10753,0,'Practice SM Chakram',0,39,11,10259,5228,'Please leave me in the Arena!','2015-12-04 16:56:58'),(7715134,4278454393,263167,10753,0,'Practice FS Chakram',0,39,11,10482,5226,'Please leave in the Arena!','2015-12-04 16:49:08'),(7715174,3137603705,263167,10753,0,'Practice SM Chakram',0,39,11,10258,5229,'Please leave me in the Arena!','2015-12-04 16:58:31'),(7715135,4278454393,263167,10753,0,'Practice FS Chakram',0,39,11,10474,5255,'Please leave me in the Arena!','2015-12-04 16:50:09'),(7715169,855902329,263167,10753,0,'Practice GK Chakram',0,39,11,10363,5260,'Please leave me in the Arena!','2015-12-04 16:53:03'),(7715167,855902329,263167,10753,0,'Practice GK Chakram',0,39,11,10382,5237,'Please leave me in the Arena!','2015-12-04 16:51:20'),(7715171,1996753017,263167,10753,0,'Practice DS Chakram',0,39,11,10562,5159,'Please leave me in the Arena!','2015-12-04 16:54:57'),(7715170,1996753017,263167,10753,0,'Practice DS Chakram',0,34,11,10432,5731,'Please leave me in the Arena!','2015-12-04 16:54:09'),(7715206,3137603705,263167,